Type of sample (e.g. Liquid>aqueous; sediment; etc.). Uses a controlled vocabulary from System for Earth Sample Registration (SESAR; https://www.geosamples.org/about/services#igsnregistration) system.

Mean decay rate. For each sampling event (e.g. SSS005_COT); the decay rate of each of the four biological replicates (e.g.SSS005_COT-1; SSS005_COT-2; SSS005_COT-3; SSS005_COT-4) are averaged. The replicate data was visually inspected to determine if there were outliers. No outliers were apparent; and therefore no values were removed from the mean. The "Mean_Missing_Reps" column indicates if a mean does not include all four replicates using a TRUE/FALSE flag where TRUE indicates one or more replicates are missing from the mean (i.e. a sample was lost).
Indication of whether all replicates (reps) are included in the calculation of the mean (with a FALSE flag) or all replicates are not included (with a TRUE flag).

Mean tensile strength. For each sampling event (e.g. SSS005_COT); the tensile strength of each of the four biological replicates (e.g.SSS005_COT-1; SSS005_COT-2; SSS005_COT-3; SSS005_COT-4) are averaged. The replicate data was visually inspected to determine if there were outliers. No outliers were apparent; and therefore no values were removed from the mean. The "Mean_Missing_Reps" column indicates if a mean does not include all four replicates using a TRUE/FALSE flag where TRUE indicates one or more replicates are missing from the mean (i.e. a sample was lost).
